{
  "stem": "10970.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had been stationed in Germany and moved to France.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because it was Rosh Hashanah, he was looking for a Jewish environment.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He felt, I guess, homesick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He and his friend, they were both Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think they had given them in their little booklets from the army where to find Jewish houses of worship and stuff.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we met on Rosh Hashanah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 1955, yeah.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I went out with his friend.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] He went out with my girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I believe he asked his-- my girlfriend, are you-- or his friend, are you interested in her?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, no, not really.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He says, can I go with her?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So this is how we started our courtship.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] oh yeah, my cousin in England, Stella, had-- was on the verge of convincing my aunt and my Uncle Gabriel from Paris to move to England.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because she really wanted me there, too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she felt it was a way to move all of us to England.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were in the process of doing that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But, of course, when I told them that I had met a young man, I called them up and said, I'm going to be marrying an American.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They said, don't do anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We'll be here next weekend.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] They came to Paris, tried to stop it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I believe they offered him money.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, that's all they had to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And we were married the next October.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I guess they realized they couldn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They actually even offered the two of us to move to England, which we promptly refused, you know--",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
